{
  "stem": "14060.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there are people, maybe of the later generation, who are not in that way inclined.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the problem is, they've got to live with the knowledge that their fathers, their grandfathers, their cousins, their uncles, they're all killers, one way or the other.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, as I said to you when we had our pre-interview discussion, that unfortunately, we Jews are accused that we have a chip on our shoulder.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I think if you really look at it in the contemporary history of my times, that there were really three sort of non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were the ones who had the opportunity to kill and did.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The ones who didn't have the opportunity, but we don't know if they would have killed, and probably yes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then there are some of the really [NON-ENGLISH], you call the the, the, the Righteous Gentiles in small minority.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I'm not saying that they all did it for money.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Some maybe did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Nevertheless, even if they did it for money, they were a lifesaver.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Unfortunately, in Hungary, the numbers of individuals who were hidden in percentage was minute compared even to Poland-- which Poland is certainly not known to be [LAUGHS] a nation of friends of Jews.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And therefore, what I want to make on this point is that we lived in an-- in an alien circumstances, believing that we are part of the country.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I must say that, in my time, we-- whilst we were decent citizens and everything else, we did not anymore believe that they are really taking care of us, or they would defend us in any way.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "However, we believed that it won't happen to us because of the gradual, step-by-step turning the screw.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
